This approach systematically checks for the presence of specific structural sub-components within the input. It extracts potential types using nav logic and delegates to specialized functions based on what is found first.

```python
def build_type(s_dt):
    '''
    Build a partial xsd tree out of a S_DT and its sub types S_CDT, S_EDT, S_SDT and S_UDT.
    '''
    s_cdt = nav_one(s_dt).S_CDT[17]()
    if s_cdt:
        return build_core_type(s_cdt)

    s_edt = nav_one(s_dt).S_EDT[17]()
    if s_edt:
        return build_enum_type(s_edt)

    s_udt = nav_one(s_dt).S_UDT[17]()
    if s_udt:
        return build_user_type(s_udt)
```

The function prioritizes checking the core type (`S_CDT`) over the others. If multiple types were present, only the first check that evaluates true will execute, establishing a clear hierarchy of evaluation.
